<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-640-430  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 640 430.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  August 16 1989 n113 p68(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business and Computer Publications1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>4Views. (Software Review) (4-5-6 World's add-in data base forLotus 1-2-3 2.0)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Walsh, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   4-5-6 World (products).andO;Product:   4Views (Data base management system).andO;Topic:     EvaluationAdd-In-On SoftwareData Base Management Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>FOURWORD is an add-in word processor for Lotus 1-2-3 Release 2.0, 2.01 anddie planned 2.2.andP;  It can be attached using the standard ADD-MGR program, andonce you have copied its files to die Lotus subdirectory startup is automaticor invoked manually via the hotkey.andP;  You also need to run the 4NSTALL programto define the print enhancements.andM;The package has many word processing functions, including word wrap,paragraph reformatting, search and replace, and block moves, butspellchecking is missing.andP;  A useful feature is the ability to hotkey fromspreadsheet to document view, and even hotlink parts of the spreadsheet intothe document.andM;4WORD constantly monitors the ranges in your spreadsheet to check if you'vechanged them.andP;  if you do make a change, it puts a LINK indicator at die footof the screen.andP;  You should note that 4WORD only monitors die first 200 cellsin each linked spreadsheet range.andM;To print, you use 1-2-3's Print command in die usual manner, making sure thatyou select die entire width of the long labels making up your 4WORD document.andO;This is especially important when your document contains print attributeswhich can cause lines to extend beyond the norinal right margin.andM;Various text enhancements are offered by 4WORD, such as bold, italics andunderline.andP;  you can also place setup strings direcdy in the spreadsheet;simply precede the setup string  with two split vertical ban (||).andP;  Forexample place || \015 in a spreadsheet cell above an extra-wide 4woRD link toprint the linked block in compressed print.andM;4GRAPH is a companion add-in supplied with 4WORD, which lets you insertgraphs into your 1-2-3 output, as well as both 4WORD documents and regularspreadsheet prints.andP;  It works with PIC files created using the/Graph Savecommand.andM;You specify a graph format line to specify size and location of your graph,then an output range must be specified.andP;  Finally, the output is saved to .PICfiles ready for printing.andP;  You win have to exit 1-2-3 and use PrintGraph toactu- ally print the graph.andO;</TEXT></DOC>